---
import banner from "@/src/assets/images/banners/Emerging_Tech_Banner.png";
import PageLayout from "@/src/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import base_url from "@/src/lib/base_url";
---

<PageLayout title="What Are AI Transportation Use Cases" bannerImage={banner}>
  <Fragment slot="banner">What Are AI Transportation Use Cases</Fragment>
  <main>
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-4">
      <ol class="breadcrumb">
        <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href={base_url("/research-areas/artificial-intelligence/overview")}>Overview</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">What Are AI Transportation Use Cases</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="content-wrapper">
      <p class="lead">
        AI has the opportunity to serve as a transformative and strategic catalyst that could fundamentally enhance multimodal transportation. By enabling the seamless fusion of diverse data streams, AI can power superior real-time predictions and optimized decision-making, allowing transportation agencies to transition from reactive troubleshooting to proactive, "anticipatory" postures.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        At the same time, AI serves as an engine for institutional innovation, pushing the boundaries of what is possible while automating complex, high-volume tasks. The ITS JPO has categorized AI applications or use cases by transportation program and ITS service areas while highlighting illustrative (not comprehensive) use cases for each.
      </p>

      <div class="info-box mt-4">
        <h3 class="info-title">AI Use Case Categories</h3>
        <p>The ITS JPO organizes AI applications across key transportation program areas and ITS service domains, providing agencies with a structured framework to identify relevant solutions for their specific operational contexts and strategic priorities.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Transportation Program Area</th>
            <th>Sub-System / Application</th>
            <th>Key Capabilities / Use Cases</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Safety</td>
            <td>ITS Vehicle Safety</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Predictive threat intelligence</li>
                    <li>Incident detection</li>
                    <li>Adaptive threat & incident response</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Safety</td>
            <td>Public Safety</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Vehicle crash detection</li>
                    <li>Video analytics</li>
                    <li>Multi-modal detection</li>
                    <li>Crowd monitoring</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Operations & Management</td>
            <td>Traffic Management</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Signal timing & prediction</li>
                    <li>Work zone monitoring</li>
                    <li>Traffic congestion analysis</li>
                    <li>Predicting traffic bottlenecks</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Operations & Management</td>
            <td>Weather</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Incident hotspot analysis</li>
                    <li>Predictive warning systems</li>
                    <li>Weather impact assessment</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Freight</td>
            <td>Vehicle Operations</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Freight tracking and prediction</li>
                    <li>Optimal routing & scheduling</li>
                    <li>Capacity utilization prediction</li>
                    <li>Container tracking</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Freight</td>
            <td>Parking Management</td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Dynamic parking availability & prediction</li>
                    <li>Multi-modal parking integration</li>
                    <li>Demand forecasting</li>
                    <li>Pricing optimization</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Asset Management</td>
            <td></td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Road asset condition monitoring</li>
                    <li>Structural health assessment</li>
                    <li>Lifecycle cost modeling</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td></td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Pipeline integrity management</li>
                    <li>Corrosion detection</li>
                    <li>Leak detection</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td></td>
            <td>
                <ul>
                    <li>Utilities infrastructure mapping</li>
                    <li>Asset tracking and inventory</li>
                    <li>Preventative maintenance scheduling</li>
                </ul>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<!-- Note: The original input was not a clean table structure, so I had to guess the intended grouping based on common infrastructure themes. I have structured the data into a standard HTML table format for clarity, assuming the missing headers/categories were implied. -->

  </main>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .info-box {
    background: rgb(var(--color-gray-light));
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #0066cc;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .info-title {
    color: #003d7a;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .info-box p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb-item a {
    color: #0066cc;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb-item a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .breadcrumb-item.active {
    color: #666;
  }

  /* Table Styling */
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    background: white;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  thead {
    background: #003d7a;
    color: white;
  }

  thead th {
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  tbody tr {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  tbody tr:hover {
    background: #f8f9fa;
  }

  tbody tr:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  td {
    padding: 1rem;
    vertical-align: top;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  td strong {
    color: #003d7a;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* First column (Domain/Area) styling */
  tbody td:first-child {
    background: #f0f4f8;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #003d7a;
    border-right: 2px solid #0066cc;
  }

  /* Use cases column */
  .use-cases ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
  }

  .use-cases li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .use-cases li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Responsive table */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    table {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    td, th {
      padding: 0.75rem;
    }

    .use-cases ul {
      padding-left: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
